iScreen - Privacy Policy
iScreen understands the importance of your personal information, and will do our best to protect your security and reliability, and will never abuse or disclose your private information.
iScreen access to the rights and user information in accordance with the following principles: clear purpose principle, the principle of consent, the least enough principle, the principle of openness and transparency, the principle of power and responsibility.
Please read and understand the following instructions carefully before using our products:
I.What information will we collect?
Device information
Equipment information refers to the information about the equipment you use when using our products or services. For products and services and equipment to make the necessary adaptation and provide security services, when you use the product or service, will collect you use iScreen equipment name, type of product or service, equipment identification number, operating system and application version, language Settings, resolution , Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) related information. This information is collected to help us conduct bug analysis, ensure your normal use of our products and services, improve and optimize our product experience, and ensure the security of your account.
2. Location
Location information refers to the location information collected when you enable the device location function and use location-based services, including:
When you turn on the device location function and use related products or services, we may use GPS, WiFi or other technologies to collect and process information about your actual location. Our products or services will not collect such personal sensitive information unless it is required by specific product or service functions.
Real-time information about your geographic location that you or another user provide. Includes shared information that you or others upload showing your current or past geographic location, and Geo-tagged information contained in photos that you or others share. If you do not want to be accessed, you can choose to turn off the relevant functions in the device or products/services, which may affect our provision of relevant services to you.
3. Log information
For the sake of service security, when you use products and services, the system may automatically collect certain information through cookies or other means and store it in the server logs. Such information may include:
Detailed use of our products and services, such information may include the web search terms you use, the addresses of the pages you visit, and other information and content details you browse or request to provide when using the Services; Device or software information. In addition to the above device information, we may collect the version number and browser type of the software you use. We collect information about the mobile applications and other software you use to ensure the security of your operating environment or to provide services. Device event information, including crashes, system activity information, and other related information.
II.How do we use the information we collect?
We strictly abide by laws and regulations and our agreements with users, and use the information collected for the following purposes. If we use your information for more than the following purposes, we will explain to you again and obtain your consent.
1. Meet your personalized needs: for example, location setting, personalized help service.
2. Provide you with services, product development and service optimization: For example, when our system fails, we will record and analyze the information generated when the system fails to optimize our services.
3. Security: For example, we will use your information for authentication, security prevention, anti-fraud monitoring, archive backup, customer security services and other purposes. For example, the security software you download or install will detect malicious programs or viruses, or identify fraud messages for you.
4. Manage software: For example, perform software authentication and upgrade.
5. We invite you to participate in a survey about our services.
6. Collect and use your information in accordance with laws and regulations, without obtaining your authorization.
Those related to state security or national defense security;
Those related to public security, public health or major public interests;
Those relating to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments;
For the purpose of safeguarding the life, property and other important legal rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals, but it is difficult to obtain the consent of the subject;
Necessary to maintain the safe and stable operation of the provided products and/or services, including finding and disposing of faults of the products and/or services, etc.;
Necessary for legitimate news reporting;
When academic research institutions carry out statistical or academic research necessary for the public interest, and provide the results of academic research or description to the public, they de-identification the personal information contained in the results;
Other circumstances stipulated by laws and regulations.
7. Other purposes approved by you.
In order to provide you with a better experience, improve our services or for other purposes agreed by you, we may use the information collected through certain services for our other services, subject to compliance with relevant laws and regulations. For example, the information you use in one of our services can be used in another service to show you content or advertising, and for user research and analysis and statistics.
Our product integration Umeng+ SDK, Umeng+ SDK need to collect your device Mac address, the only equipment identification number (IMEI/Android ID / IDFA / OpenUDID / GUID / IP / SIM card IMSI information / Running process) statistical analysis to provide services, The accuracy of report data is calibrated by geographic location to provide basic anti-cheating capabilities. Please refer to the privacy Policy on the official website of Umeng+ for the types, uses and rules of personal information protection of the information collected by Umeng +SDK.
To ensure the security of the service and to help us better understand how our application is performing, we may record information such as how often you use the application, failure information, overall usage, performance data, and the origin of the application. We don't store the information in our analyzing software.
8. Access Apple Music and media databases. In order for you to use the "Music Player" widget in the app normally, we need you to authorize us to access Apple Music information, your music and video related activities, and your media database, such as obtaining songs currently playing on Apple Music and displaying them in the app and widgets. If you refuse authorization, you will not be able to use this feature normally, but it will not affect your use of other software features.
Our Android product third-party sdk instructions:
AndroidSupportLibraryCompat: Get SD card data for selecting pictures, setting backgrounds, and downloading wallpapers
Our Android product device permission call instructions:
Read mobile phone identification code: obtain device information as a user-related identification
Read storage space, camera: used to read, store, and take photos for background image settings
Read application installation list: used to set shortcut startup
None of the above will be enabled by default, and will only be used to achieve specific functions or services after your express authorization. You can also withdraw the authorization. It should be pointed out that even if we have obtained these sensitive permissions with your authorization, we will not collect your information when the relevant functions or services are not required.
III.Disclosure of information
Unless otherwise expressly agreed in this Policy, we will not provide your device information to any third party. However, we cannot guarantee that other third parties will not acquire your equipment information through other means and combine the equipment information with other information to identify your personal identity. If any loss is caused to you, you shall claim compensation from the third party. The above equipment information is the basic information collected for providing services. If you do not want the equipment information to be collected by us, we may not be able to provide normal services to you.
IV.Provision of information
Users of iScreen can always choose whether to disclose information or not. Some information is required to register for our services, but most other information is provided at the user's discretion. iScreen will prioritize user comfort and choice. iScreen may provide network interactive activities for users, in order to facilitate users to participate in interactive activities and get interactive prizes, iScreen usually requires applicants in the contact information (mailing address and telephone number). This kind of information is used by iScreen to accumulate user data. If the user does not want to provide the requested information and participate in such activities, this is entirely at the user's discretion.
V.Information and use of minors
iScreen recommendation: Any minor participating in online activities should obtain prior written consent from their parent or legal guardian (hereinafter referred to as the "guardian"). iScreen will protect the relevant information of minors in accordance with relevant national laws and regulations.
VI.Cookies
Through the use of Cookies, iScreen provides users with a simple and personalized web experience. A cookie is a small amount of data that is sent from a web server to your browser and stored on your computer's hard disk. iScreen uses Cookies for the benefit of its users. Cookies can help us improve the quality of service by storing user preferences, improving the user experience and tracking user trends, such as how people use iScreen. Cookies can help us determine the pages and content you connect to, the time you spend on specific pages on iScreen and the services you choose on iScreen. Cookies are id cards placed on a computer or server on iScreen. It can only be read by the server that set them up, and it can't execute any code or viruses. Cookies enable iScreen to serve you better and faster, and help you make some personalized Settings for iScreen. However, you should be able to control whether and how Cookies are accepted by your browser. Consult the documentation that comes with your browser for more information on this.
In short, iScreen treats Cookies as a convenient experience that allows users to move from one service on iScreen to another without having to prove their identity. You may refuse Cookies by modifying your browser Settings, and if you choose to refuse Cookies, you may not be able to log in to or use iScreen services or features that rely on Cookies.
VII.Seven, data security
iScreen promises to take reasonable and necessary precautions to protect the security of users' data to the extent permitted by existing technology, but none of the Internet service providers can guarantee 100% security of data, so iScreen cannot make absolute guarantees. We take the best possible measures to protect the data you store on our desktop, based on reasonable business practices. Your personal information and data are protected in multiple ways, including personal, electronic and programmatic.
If iScreen learns of a security system vulnerability, we may contact the email address you have provided us or post a notice on our website in an attempt to inform you and provide information about the protection measures (if applicable).
VIII.Update and disclose information
iScreen encourages users to update and modify their personal information to make it effective. Users can easily access and modify their personal information at any time. Users can modify or delete their information at their own discretion. Please remember that whenever you voluntarily disclose personal information (such as online disclosure), such information may be collected and used by others, thus causing the disclosure of your personal information. iScreen is not responsible for the disclosure of your personal information. If you disclose your personal information through the above channels, you may cause the disclosure of your personal information. Therefore, we remind and invite you to carefully consider whether it is necessary to disclose your personal information through the above channels.
Finally, you are the only person responsible for the confidentiality of your account and password information. In any case, please keep it carefully.
Modification and update
As this Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time, you should review it regularly to understand our programs and procedures for protecting the personal information we collect. Your continued use of iScreen Services constitutes your consent to this Privacy Policy and any updates thereto. Please contact us with questions about this statement or iScreen's privacy measures.
Company name: Xiamen 01 World Technology Co., LTD
Company address: Unit 902, Building A, Zhongwaiyun Building, No. 1032, Xiahe Road, Siming District, Xiamen city
This Privacy Policy will be updated and effective on December 18, 2020.
